f all how deeply honored I feel by the invitation in your letter of February 21 to serve as Honorary Consultant in American Letters.

With reluctance and regret, I must decline this honor. I lack the necessary energy and aptitude to be of any practical use to the Library. I would not be able to acquit myself properly even of the very limited duties you outline; and my conscience forbids me to accept your offer while knowing that I should not be able to force myself to write a single letter or re